21 April 2015The Film and Publication Board (FPB) is conducting national public engagements to allow South Africans the opportunity to give input on the draft Online Regulation Policy. The consultations begin in April through to June 2015.The draft policy is available for viewing and comment on the FPB website at www.fpb.org.za. The FPB invites the public to view the policy and submit their comments, as well as to attend the engagements happening in the various provinces.Members of the media are invited to attend the event as follows: Date: 23 April 2015 Time: 17h00 Venue: Artscape Theatre, D.F Malan Street, Foreshore, Cape TownIssued by Government Communication and Information System on behalf of the Film and Publication Board